      "content": "<p>SEO platforms combine several data sources and estimation methods. The interface may look precise, but keyword volumes, difficulty scores and traffic estimates should be treated as directional rather than guaranteed.</p><h2>Keyword research</h2><p>Check the supported countries, languages, update frequency and export limits. Compare a small sample against your existing data sources.</p><h2>Site audit</h2><p>A useful audit should separate critical technical issues from low-priority warnings and explain why each issue matters.</p><h2>Reporting</h2><p>Agency users should inspect white-label options, scheduled reporting, project limits and client access before choosing a plan.</p><h2>Final verdict</h2><p>The platform may save time when its reports match your workflow. It should not replace analytics, search-console data or experienced technical review.</p>"
